726294f-c.text:
Calamus Ave. (across front of peaked roof house in foreground), between Ankener Ave. (riht) and Elks Road (left), showing in the foreground the Rapelye farmhouse. Across from it are two homes, Nos. 7481 and 7d42 Calamus Ave. This is a set of four views, showing also general views northwest with Queens Boulevard in the background.
January 1924.
Eucene L. Armbruster Collection.

726292f-b.text:
Calamus Ave., west from Ankener Ave., showing in the foreoround the Rapelje farmhouse and outbuildings. Note the winding turns of Calamus Ave. In the background is the elevated structure, at about 47th Street, of the New York Connecting Railroad. This is a set of
three views.
January 1923.
View 2: January 1924.
View 3: September 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster.
